An indefinite strike by 47,000carworkers on Tuesday closed most Brazilian plants ofAutolatina, the company said.    Autolatina, one of the world's largest automakers, said ithad offered its employees a pay rise of 20.66 pct, adding thatthe workers were pressing for a 65.9 pct rise.    The strike is the first to hit operations of Autolatinasince it formally came into existence on July 1. The companygroups Ford and Volkswagen in Brazil and Argentina.    A spokesman said factories in Argentina were unaffected. Hesaid about 9,000 of the company's 55,900 employees in Brazilwere still working and some production was continuing. Reuter&#3;